1
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:36,840
♪ I was like a sun without rays of light ♪

2
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:39,840
♪ I never mattered ♪

3
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:44,920
♪ With no one to rely on ♪

4
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:50,360
♪ Until you came along and changed everything in me ♪

5
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:53,680
♪ Helped me find true love ♪

6
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:57,560
♪ And realize who to live for ♪

7
00:00:58,360 --> 00:01:01,640
♪ Once looked lonely ♪

8
00:01:01,720 --> 00:01:04,360
♪ I'm now filled with your shadow ♪

9
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:10,280
♪ As the light to my heart ♪

10
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:16,160
♪ You are the moon in my heart ♪

11
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:20,800
♪ You make everything ♪

12
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:24,800
♪ More meaningful every day ♪

13
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:30,440
♪ I wanna be your sun ♪

14
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:34,280
♪ Please let me ♪

15
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:40,800
♪ Be by your side
And keep on loving you ♪

16
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,560
I no longer trust your company.

17
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:48,160
I'll find my daughter's bodyguard myself.

18
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:49,840
As far as I know,

19
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:52,520
no one meets the VIP's criteria at all.

20
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:55,080
I don't think we need to look for
another company, Dad.

21
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,160
Looking forward to working with you,

22
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:58,320
Ms. Bodyguard.

23
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:00,120
We have additional rules.

24
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:03,240
Always stay in the bodyguard's line of sight.

25
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:05,520
How far is the line of sight?

26
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,560
Am I in your sight now?

27
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,960
This shop makes great congee.

28
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:13,800
I bought it and came straight here.

29
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:17,560
My treat, because you just bought me congee.

30
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:19,920
Whoa, Mic!

31
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:24,320
Tawan, that's Mic. He's a son of a maid here.

32
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:27,960
He likes to buy me snacks because he's my fan.

33
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:38,680
Let me check your neck.

34
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,040
It's okay. I'm fine now.

35
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:42,800
I'm gonna take my leave.

36
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:56,560
I have many types of fans.

37
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:02,880
Some can't look me in the eye,
can't get close, can't touch me,

38
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:09,760
Some are happy just from seeing me in videos
and hearing my voice on screens.

39
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:14,680
Some haven't seen me in real life but love me so much.

40
00:03:15,640 --> 00:03:20,360
Their goodwill and love for me
are my significant source of support.

41
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:25,480
What about those who send you horrible things
and keep harassing you?

42
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,160
To be honest,

43
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:33,360
that happened to me recently.

44
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:36,320
Some send me death threats.

45
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,800
Some say they want me out of show business.

46
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:41,160
Some send me bloody dolls.

47
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:46,120
I tried to think if I had wronged someone,

48
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:49,160
but in the end I couldn't think of any.

49
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:51,480
I'm sure I never hurt anyone first.

50
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:54,920
Maybe you didn't wrong anyone at all.

51
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:58,200
But those who are jealous of you...

52
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,520
may hurt you.

53
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,000
Probably the anti-fans.

54
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:24,280
Oh, pretty lady.

55
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:26,240
-Hello, Yam.
-Hello.

56
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,200
You're not done rehearsing?

57
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:30,240
Just one more verse.

58
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:35,400
Hey, Ayla, your new song is so beautiful. I love it.

59
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:38,080
You listened to it?
I thought they weren't done mixing it.

60
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:42,960
Oh, that's right. You're right. They're not.

61
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:47,080
But I'm your number one fan, so I asked to listen in.

62
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:51,360
Well, go back to your rehearsal.
I can rehearse in the afternoon instead.

63
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:55,040
You don't have to do that.
I'll leave right now so you can start.

64
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:58,880
Wow. Goodness gracious.

65
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:02,520
You're the number one artist
and you rehearse so hard.

66
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:06,280
I'm just a minnow. I can wait.

67
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:09,000
Oi, what number one?

68
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:12,640
I'm not. Go ahead. I'm scheduled
in the recording studio anyway.

69
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,720
All right, all right, you got it.

70
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,200
-See you around.
-See you, sis.

71
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,760
-Bye.
-Bye.

72
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,760
Ayla?

73
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,880
Your scheduled visitor's here.

74
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:39,040
Okay.

75
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,960
Been waiting long, Khaotu?

76
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:58,520
Not at all. Are you off work?

77
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,040
I am.

78
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,000
Hey,

79
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,000
there's someone I want you to meet.

80
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,400
Tawan!

81
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,600
Tawan!

82
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,560
Tawan.

83
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,640
This is really her, right?

84
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:21,800
Of course.

85
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:25,520
The one and only. No one is more beautiful.

86
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:29,640
You're still as cool as ever.

87
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,800
I hope you're doing well.

88
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,040
I am.

89
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,880
And you, Khaotu? How have you been?

90
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:41,760
I'm a beautiful flight attendant now, Tawan.

91
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:46,400
This idol pestered me to come
and hang out in her office today.

92
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:49,440
Who was pestering who? Don't lie to Tawan.

93
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,480
All right, all right.

94
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:54,480
I was pestering her.

95
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,480
But you owe me dinner for my birthday.

96
00:06:56,560 --> 00:07:00,160
Eh? You're always flying like a bird.
It's hard to line up our schedules.

97
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,960
I'm an angel, not a bird.

98
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:04,240
There's a fine line between angels and birds.

99
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:06,880
There's no line here. I'm an angel with wings.

100
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,920
-You can easily be a bird.
-No way.

101
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:11,200
I'm so pretty. I have to be an angel.

102
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:43,360
Hey! What the hell? Hey! Get off me!

103
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,560
Get off me!

104
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:47,040
Hey, that's my property!

105
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,560
-Whoa.
-Give it back!

106
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:52,760
You're caught red-handed. I suggest you shut up.

107
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,840
Not a sasaeng fan, boss, but a paparazzo.

108
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:01,680
Take care of it and coordinate with Ayla's team.

109
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,360
Copy, boss.

110
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:08,320
It's been taken care of. You can get in the van.

111
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:12,400
Tawan, are those your staffs?

112
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,240
Wow, they're so cool.

113
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,720
I only ever see that in action movies.

114
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:20,680
Can you do that move for me?

115
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:21,800
-That move...
-Oi!

116
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:24,200
-Ugh!
-I'm freaking starving.

117
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,880
Not the time to ask for a reenactment. Let's eat!

118
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:30,240
All right, all right. My car's over there.

119
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:32,360
-See you at the restaurant.
-See you there.

120
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,600
-See you.
-See you.

121
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,520
Thank you.

122
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,320
Huh?

123
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:52,800
What?

124
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,360
Huh?

125
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:06,280
(Phitsanulok)

126
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:15,160
Hey.

127
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:19,840
Ayla, are you all right?

128
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,240
I'm... I'm fine.

129
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:23,160
What about you?

130
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,600
Whoa.

131
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,360
Ayla.

132
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:01,360
I'm fine.

133
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,200
See?

134
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,280
It's nothing.

135
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,120
But you're still hurt.

136
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:24,200
♪ I was like a sun without rays of light ♪

137
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:27,440
♪ I never mattered ♪

138
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:32,280
♪ With no one to rely on ♪

139
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:37,720
♪ Until you came along and changed everything in me ♪

140
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:40,640
♪ Helped me find true love ♪

141
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:45,480
♪ And realize who to live for ♪

142
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:49,160
♪ Once looked lonely ♪

143
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:51,800
♪ I'm now filled with your shadow ♪

144
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:57,960
♪ As the light to my heart ♪

145
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:03,400
♪ You are the moon in my heart ♪

146
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,640
I called the hospital, boss.

147
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,160
Here.

148
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:12,320
♪ More meaningful every day ♪

149
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:17,800
♪ I wanna be your sun ♪

150
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:21,600
♪ Please let me ♪

151
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:24,760
♪ Be by your side and keep on loving you ♪

152
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:27,120
Tawan, Ayla, how are you guys?

153
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:30,840
You should go home.

154
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,160
No, I'm worried about you.

155
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:35,840
Trust me. Go home. I'll call you.

156
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,360
Okay.

157
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:41,520
But Tawan, you were super cool earlier.

158
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:49,040
Ayla! You're really fine, right?

159
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,720
Ugh, it's so scary.

160
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:58,160
I'm fine. Fortunately, she saved me.

161
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,680
So...

162
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:03,640
I'm gonna take her to the hospital.

163
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:05,840
I'm coming with you.

164
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:09,160
If I let you go like this,
Boss will kill me if she finds out.

165
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:13,160
We'll take good care of Ms. Ayla. Don't worry.

166
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,120
But I...

167
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:20,360
That's right. If Boss has any questions,
she can call me. Don't worry.

168
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:24,760
-Take care of yourself.
-Goodbye. Goodbye.

169
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:31,920
Tawan?

170
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:33,440
Tawan?

171
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,680
How are you doing?

172
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:38,240
The doctor said it wasn't bad.

173
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,800
Because we dressed the wound well.

174
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:47,280
It should get better in a few days.

175
00:12:48,520 --> 00:12:51,680
Nana's looking into the bike's registration plate.

176
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:52,840
Good.

177
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,400
Do it as quickly as possible.

178
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:55,840
Yes, boss.

179
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:58,080
In the next few days,

180
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:01,760
I'll get more people to take care of you.

181
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,720
Not a problem at all.

182
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:05,600
That way you can rest.

183
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:07,880
I'll be there.

184
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:11,840
I'm just

185
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,480
adding more people.

186
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:23,840
Ms. Rawee, please come to the cashier's office.

187
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:33,760
This is against the rules.

188
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:36,000
Boss shouldn't be doing this.

189
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:39,520
I know.

190
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:42,880
The meds she took are strong. She'll sleep in no time.

191
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:44,400
Why won't she just rest?

192
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:47,640
The rules say you rest when you're hurt.

193
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:49,920
We're available. We can take her place.

194
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:52,200
This is getting weird.

195
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:56,080
I think this whole thing is fishy.

196
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:03,800
Where's Boss?

197
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,760
-Why are you here?
-Why are you here?

198
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:10,600
Eh? She called me here. Said she needed support.

199
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:14,160
-Emotional support, maybe.
-Don't know.

200
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:14,880
Well...

201
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:16,960
So where is she?

202
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:17,760
Over there.

203
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:24,160
Don't even think about it. Come here. Just come here.

204
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:06,800
-Downstairs clear.
-All clear.

205
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:12,640
Tawan, then why don't you get some rest?

206
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,680
Boss?

207
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:18,720
We'll take care of Ms. Ayla. Don't worry.

208
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,200
Please get some rest.

209
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:24,480
Well?

210
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:46,880
Guys, Rule 27 is in effect as of now.

211
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,760
Except for going out. In that case, come get me.

212
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,400
Copy, boss.

213
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,080
I'm counting on you.

214
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,280
-Yes, boss.
-Yes.

215
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:11,240
Can I get her medicine?

216
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,840
You guys can make yourselves at home.

217
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:29,800
Are you hungry? I can order you food.

218
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:33,600
Under the circumstances, it's better if we make the order.

219
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,840
I can guarantee the food will be good and safe.

220
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:40,520
What would you like, Ms. Ayla?

221
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:42,240
What's Tawan's favorite food?

222
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:48,280
I'll eat whatever she eats.

223
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:52,040
You want everything that Boss loves?

224
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:56,040
That's right. You can order two or three sets.

225
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,200
Your meds before bed.

226
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:36,960
And here are your PJs.

227
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:49,280
If you need anything,

228
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:50,960
you can call me anytime.

229
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:18,880
(Carbonara, Spaghetti with tomato sauce,
dry noodles, pork noodles, Pork Pad Thai)

230
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:24,920
We made deals with these restaurants.

231
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:26,880
Definitely delicious and safe, Ms. Ayla.

232
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,000
-Go ahead and order.
-I see.

233
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:30,680
I will.

234
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:40,480
Um, Ms. Ayla?

235
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:42,480
Yes? Oh.

236
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:43,520
You want something?

237
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:45,320
Oh.

238
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:49,760
That's a lot already. We might not be able to finish it.

239
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:54,040
There are a few of us here. Let's order a lot in case.

240
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:59,760
Besides, I don't know what Tawan likes.

241
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:02,600
Oh, Boss eats everything.

242
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:04,480
Really?

243
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:06,080
Yes.

244
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:11,080
Guys, why don't you come and sit down?

245
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:19,160
Tawan said the security system
in this room was excellent.

246
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,360
You can sit down.

247
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:27,800
We'd better not, because we're currently on duty.

248
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:31,200
Oh, she's asleep by now.

249
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:33,440
It's okay. Sit and chat with me.

250
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:42,920
I was Tawan's underclassman in high school.

251
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:46,920
-I knew it!
-I knew it!

252
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:49,800
-Excuse me, Ms. Ayla.
-No wonder.

253
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,040
Okay.

254
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,560
Yes.

255
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:08,560
Ms. Ayla, you've known each other since high school?

256
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:09,560
Eh?

257
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:12,160
Tawan never told you guys?

258
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:17,480
Never.

259
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:20,080
Oh, but we did ask her.

260
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:23,200
Boss just said you'd known each other a long time ago.

261
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:27,360
That's true. Eight years ago.

262
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:29,480
-Whoa, eight years.
-Eight years.

263
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,080
Eh?

264
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:35,040
What should I order for Tawan?

265
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:40,120
She loves noodles.

266
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:42,400
Exactly. All kinds and nationalities.

267
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:46,760
Great. In that case...

268
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,800
Thai suki soup, Thai suki stir-fry,

269
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:51,120
spaghetti with tomato sauce, carbonara,
dry noodles, pork noodles.

270
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:53,440
egg noodles with BBQ pork.

271
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:54,440
-Ah!
-Ah!

272
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:03,680
I'm very lucky Tawan agreed to be my bodyguard.

273
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:06,880
We were confused at first.

274
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:11,160
Because lately she hasn't accepted
personal protection details like this.

275
00:21:11,160 --> 00:21:17,600
Except for the heads of states who worked
with us before and specifically request her.

276
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:18,920
Exactly.

277
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:20,360
And now she's injured.

278
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:23,720
Usually we would change personnel
or give you a new team.

279
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:25,240
But she wouldn't do that.

280
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:28,320
Instead, she made an exception by adding us.

281
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,520
So your case must be very important to her.

282
00:21:33,520 --> 00:21:36,480
Responsibility must be very important to her.

283
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:40,680
She promised to take care of me,
so she doesn't want to fail.

284
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:42,040
That's right.

285
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:45,120
She's very strict and a perfectionist.

286
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:47,160
She doesn't want mistakes to happen.

287
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:50,600
And nothing, no matter how small, gets past her.

288
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,680
So...

289
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:58,560
how did you guys come to work for Tawan?

290
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:01,120
I was in the military.

291
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:03,200
I was a Navy SEAL.

292
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:06,360
And I was the top of my class.

293
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:08,960
As for me,

294
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:13,960
I might not look it now, but I was a nerdy kid.

295
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:16,480
To the point I stopped talking to people.

296
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:19,040
I had too much fun writing computer codes.

297
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:20,800
So talented.

298
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:24,760
Hey, I'm actually a very low-tech person.

299
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:27,200
I know only music-related technologies.

300
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,520
But when it comes to the computer stuff,

301
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:30,600
I'm useless.

302
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,360
Zero.

303
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:35,200
Back then, Boss had just returned from Hong Kong.

304
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:37,720
Hong Kong?

305
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:42,440
Yes, she was looking for someone
to head the IT department.

306
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:44,800
Someone recommended me,

307
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,360
so she reached out.

308
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:51,360
At first I was only in charge of finding information.

309
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:55,400
The next thing I knew,
Boss'd lured me into being a bodyguard.

310
00:22:58,680 --> 00:22:59,880
So...

311
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:02,920
did Tawan live in Hong Kong long?

312
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,760
Quite long.

313
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:09,440
And when she speaks Chinese,
no one believes that she's Thai.

314
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:13,480
She speaks many languages. At least... five.

315
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:14,960
She's so talented.

316
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:16,960
What about you, Chanya?

317
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:18,880
I'm an ex-cop.

318
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:21,600
I quit and came to work for Boss.

319
00:23:21,680 --> 00:23:24,840
I thought this job would fit me better.

320
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:28,160
So you're independent and hates being forced.

321
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:33,240
Boss said the exact same thing.

322
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,840
Am I that transparent?

323
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:37,440
Really?

324
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:38,240
-Yes.
-Yes.

325
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:45,560
Tawan works a lot.

326
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:47,520
Doesn't her partner mind?
